name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: The #AmericanJobsPlan is a game-changer and full of ideas that progressives like me are fighting for to make long-overdue investments in America’s future.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: I’ve also called for a Real Corporate Profits Tax to ensure that giant companies that report billions of dollars in profits don’t exploit loopholes to pay close to nothing in taxes. President Biden’s plan includes a version of this policy.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: I’ve got lots of ways to make big corporations and the ultra-rich pay their fair share for these investments, like raising the top corporate tax rate, stopping tax haven abuse and offshoring, and bolstering the IRS. The President's plan includes all these ideas.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: And I announced a bill with @RepAndyLevin to use the enormous purchasing power of the US government to kick-start demand for American-made clean energy products and create good jobs. President Biden’s plan is a good first step toward the goal.

tweet: My #BuildGreen Act would electrify our public transportation to create jobs, modernize our crumbling infrastructure, and fight the #ClimateCrisis. President Biden’s proposal has the first round of funding we need to make our plan a reality.

tweet: I’ve introduced a housing bill to build millions of new housing units, and a bill to take care of our badly-needed public housing repairs. President Biden’s plan gets us a good part of the way there to create jobs and make housing more affordable.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: I’ve been sounding the alarm long before COVID about the big, structural investments that we need to make child care part of our basic infrastructure. President Biden’s plan invests in child care facilities and availability, a good first step on the path to universal care.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: The #AmericanRescueAct is just the start of the bold policies and big, structural changes that Congress can make for working families. You bet I’m in this fight to build opportunity for all of our families.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: There’s a lot of other important pieces in this relief bill for Massachusetts. Stimulus and unemployment checks. Expansion of the Child Tax Credit and Earned Income Tax Credit. LIHEAP funding. SNAP benefits and school meal funding. It's a long bill full of great stuff.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Our mass transit systems are critical infrastructure for our cities and towns, but COVID has created budget nightmares. Massachusetts will receive over $1 billion in relief for our mass transit systems for operating expenses, payroll costs, and protective equipment.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Restaurants have been crushed all year, and this bill has some real support. The $25 billion Restaurant Revitalization Fund helps small restaurant owners in Massachusetts and nationwide. And it expands the PPP program by $7.25 billion with more flexibility and forgiveness.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: With millions of people still out of work during this crisis, cash-strapped families have struggled to keep a roof over their heads. Massachusetts will receive $362 million in emergency rental assistance to help stop a wave of evictions.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: To help our schools safely reopen, the relief bill includes $1.8 billion in Elementary and Secondary School Emergency Relief funding for Massachusetts. And for our older students, it has $825 million for MA colleges, including millions to help students with financial aid grants.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: We need child care for parents to go back to work – and I fought for $50 billion in child care funding nationwide. Massachusetts is going to see $512 million to support child care providers and help families afford care, and $13.6 million for Head Start.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Our state and local governments had to pick up the tab when Trump didn't come up with a federal plan to fight this pandemic. The relief bill has $8.1 billion for Massachusetts state and local government funding with much more flexibility than the CARES Act.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: The #AmericanRescueAct is a historic piece of legislation for our country’s recovery from this pandemic and economic crisis. But I want to take a moment to mention some of the big wins we fought for to help families back home in Massachusetts:

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Today we remember the family, friends, and neighbors we loved – and we search for a way to settle this loss in our hearts. We need each other more than ever, working together to build tomorrow, and the next day, and the next day, with opportunities for better days ahead.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: On this one-year anniversary, I’m optimistic about the future. We have vaccines and a strong relief package on the way. The numbers are looking better. But our hearts still hurt from everything and everyone that this pandemic has stolen from us.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: And our essential workers – including grocery store workers, farm workers, warehouse workers, meatpacking workers, restaurant workers, and delivery workers – have risked their health in the scariest conditions to keep us safe and fed. We’re in their debt.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Our doctors, nurses, hospital staff, public health experts and scientists have worked around the clock, one grueling day after another, to stop the virus. They’ve carried the weight of the world on their shoulders – our hopes and our heartbreak. They deserve our thanks every day.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: When the WHO declared COVID-19 a global pandemic one year ago today, our country didn’t know what was around the corner. Over half a million lives lost. Tens of millions sick. Jobs gone and businesses shuttered. Unthinkable grief without hugs for comfort.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Even before the pandemic hit, Americans were already hanging on by their fingernails. In the last 40 years, consumer credit skyrocketed. People took on more debt to deal with stagnant wages and increasing costs of housing, education, medical care, and child care. #FixBankruptcy

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: It’s time to stitch up the loopholes that allow the wealthy to exploit the bankruptcy system. And we need to crack down on predatory debt collection practices and hold corporate wrongdoers accountable in court. #FixBankruptcy

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: We also need to address racial and gender disparities in the bankruptcy system. That includes letting people discharge certain criminal justice fines but preventing the discharge of debts from civil rights violations, and exempting alimony and child support income. #FixBankruptcy

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Our bill helps bankruptcy filers care for their families by helping renters with back rent avoid eviction, making student loan debt dischargeable, and letting people protect their homes and cars during the bankruptcy process. #FixBankruptcy

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: 1/3 of Latinx borrowers default on their student loans, and Black borrowers have about a 50-50 chance of defaulting on their loans. In fact, a decade after they start school, the typical Black borrower owes more on their loan than they originally borrowed. #CancelStudentDebt

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: For many systemic reasons, Black and Latinx households have a lot less wealth that white households. These students are more likely to borrow money to go to college, borrow more money while in college, and have a harder time paying when they leave college. #CancelStudentDebt

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: #10: Corporations getting taxpayer money should be held accountable for meeting their responsibilities to workers, & workers should have a stake in how funds are used. CEOs should have to certify they’re in compliance with these rules or face penalties. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

name: Elizabeth Warren

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: #8: Congress must ensure that essential workers have access to reliable, safe, healthy, & high-quality child care, & commit robust funding to help struggling child care providers during this pandemic. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

tweet: #7: All essential workers should get the care they need, whether they’re insured or not & regardless of their immigration status. We must use public programs to provide no-cost health care coverage & also fully subsidize 15 months of COBRA. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: #6: No more misclassifying employees as independent contractors to avoid providing basic benefits & protections. Congress should crack down on worker misclassification. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: #5: Whistleblowers need real protections. Workers who witness unsafe conditions on the job or know about workplace coronavirus exposure must be able to openly identify their concerns & have them addressed, without fear of retaliation. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

tweet: #4: Workers need truly universal paid sick leave & family & medical leave. Congress must pass @PattyMurray’s bill to provide 14 paid sick days & 12 weeks paid family & medical leave that President Trump cannot arbitrarily exclude workers from. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: #3: Collective bargaining agreements must be protected from being changed or dissolved during this crisis, including during any bankruptcy proceedings. And workers’ rights to vote to unionize must be protected during the pandemic. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: #2: Every worker should be paid a livable wage, & essential employees are no exception. On top of that, they should be paid robust premium pay retroactive to the start date of the pandemic. And premium pay should be higher for the lowest-wage workers. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: #1: Employers must be required to provide personal protective equipment at no cost to workers, including contractors & subcontractors. And they must have protocols for informing employees & evacuating & cleaning the site if there is COVID-19 exposure. #ProtectEssentialWorkers

tweet: MA has the world’s best health care providers & public health leaders doing everything they can to stem the COVID-19 pandemic. But the President & his admin have failed them at every turn. Read the letter @SenMarkey & I sent President Trump yesterday.  https://t.co/WfVrows0pi

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: The Trump administration mishandled its coronavirus response, but our problems aren’t insurmountable. We need diagnostics. We need information. We need personnel. And we need Congress to step up and help provide them – right now.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Congress should require @HHSgov to report demographic info for people tested to make sure tests are being distributed equally. And manufacturers should have to report their test capacity & resources daily so our federal response is accurate & communities aren’t being left behind.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Congress can also boost funding for the Public Health Service Commissioned Corps to hire and train temporary workers to administer tests. There are tasks that don’t require medical degrees & plenty of people temporarily out of work who can receive on-the-job training.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Next, Congress can also help end the testing logjam by creating a dedicated test fund to issue guaranteed contracts with public & private manufacturers. And it should provide grants for cash-strapped public health labs & doctors’ offices to purchase test equipment.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Congress can put its foot down & force President Trump to use the Defense Production Act to develop tests, the raw materials needed for those tests, and the protective equipment necessary for health care professionals to administer them. @SenatorBaldwin’s bill would do just that.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Congress is about to finish its third coronavirus package. It’s not time for us to go home. It’s time for us to dramatically increase coronavirus testing capacity. I’ve outlined the steps to move us toward this long overdue goal.  https://t.co/BMBD1gGFwn

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Restarting our economy will require one thing above all else – testing. Testing to show who's currently infected. Testing to show who's had the virus and is immune. Social distancing won't end because it's Easter. It'll end when we have sufficient testing. Here’s how we do it.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: I won’t block vital aid but tomorrow we get back up and continue the fight. And I make you this promise: I will spend every waking moment watching the Trump Administration and do everything I can to hold it accountable for how it spends this $450 billion taxpayer fund.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: But the price of action during a health crisis shouldn’t be a $450 billion Trump Administration fund that could be used to boost favored corporations. I fought for more oversight & restrictions on this fund. We got some limits, but they are short of what’s needed.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: We face a public health crisis that threatens to bring another Great Depression. Families, hospitals, & small businesses need immediate aid. This is not the bill I wanted, but its immediate investments are vital. They are also insufficient. We will need to do more – and soon.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Thanks @RepDean, I'm glad to fight alongside you for students and families.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: The rules that Senator McConnell & the Republicans rammed through the Senate tonight are designed to protect President Trump – not guarantee a fair & honest impeachment trial. The rules are rigged.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s 11th amendment allows Chief Justice Roberts – a neutral party – to approve witnesses & evidence that are relevant to the impeachment charges.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Senator Schumer’s tenth amendment gives each side 24 hours to respond to written motions – not 2 hours as provided in Senator McConnell’s rules. This should be simple – people should have time to read what they're responding to.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Senator Schumer’s ninth amendment eliminates an obstacle in Senator McConnell's rules and provides a vote on any motion to subpoena witnesses & documents after the impeachment trial question period. No further debates needed.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s eighth amendment will subpoena former National Security Advisor John Bolton, who has already said that he’s willing to testify about the “many relevant meetings & conversations” he knew about relating to Ukraine. McConnell should let him testify in the Senate.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer's seventh amendment is short but important: the President doesn't get to pick & choose which evidence he provides to the Senate. If he wants docs admitted, he must turn over everything asked for in the subpoena. This helps prevent selective admission of evidence.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s amendment will also subpoena Michael Duffey from OMB. 90 minutes after President Trump’s July call with Ukraine's President, Duffey told the Pentagon not to release the aid to Ukraine that Congress had approved & to keep quiet about it. He should also testify.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s sixth amendment will subpoena Robert Blair, an advisor to acting WH Chief of Staff Mulvaney, who was on the line during President Trump’s July call with the Ukrainian President. He refused to testify in the House. He should testify in the Senate trial.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Let’s be clear: we wouldn’t be holding amendment votes at 10pm if Senator McConnell and the Senate Republicans weren’t rigging the rules of this impeachment trial.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s fifth amendment will subpoena “all documents, communications, and other records within the possession, custody, or control of the Department of Defense” related to Ukraine. We should see all evidence of the orders that the Pentagon received to freeze Ukraine's aid.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s fourth amendment will subpoena acting WH Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney. Several officials testified that Mulvaney organized & carried out the President’s request to withhold aid from Ukraine over the investigation of his political opponents. Mulvaney should testify.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: After 3 amendments, every GOP senator has voted: ❌No on subpoenas for White House documents ❌No on subpoenas for State Dept documents ❌ No on subpoenas for OMB documents This is a sham trial.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s third amendment will subpoena “all documents, communications, and other records within the possession, custody, or control of the Office of Management and Budget” related to Ukraine. An OMB official told the Pentagon to hold Ukraine's aid – we need that evidence.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: So here’s where we are: the Senate GOP won’t subpoena documents from the White House – and won’t subpoena documents from the State Department. If they truly believe in a fair impeachment trial, why are they hiding evidence?

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s second amendment will subpoena “all documents, communications, and other records within the possession, custody, or control of the Department of State” related to Ukraine. Once again, the @SenateGOP should stop aiding the President’s obstruction of justice.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: A trial without all of the evidence isn't a trial – it's a cover-up.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Sen. Schumer’s first amendment will subpoena “all documents, communications, and other records within the possession, custody, or control of the White House” related to Ukraine. The @SenateGOP must stop helping the President obstruct justice & bring those documents to the Senate.

name: Elizabeth Warren
tweet: Senator McConnell’s rules for the impeachment trial don’t guarantee votes on witnesses or documents after the arguments are heard. We need those votes now, at the beginning of the trial.
